   MCGRAW-HILL RYERSON Ltd. (Toronto) -- Michael G.
Richardson was named president and chief executive officer,
succeeding Robert M. Freeman, who left the company. The
publishing company said Mr. Richardson will remain an
executive vice president with the parent company, McGraw-Hill
Inc., which holds about 70% of the Canadian concern. Mr.
Richardson was president of the Canadian subsidiary in 1986
and 1987. He was then promoted to the position of president
of International Book Group and replaced as president of the
Canadian unit by Mr. Freeman.
